criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Had wounds to be healed by secondary intention,

          -  could speak Chinese,

          -  with an abbreviated mental test score 7 or above indicating their normal cognitive
             ability; and

          -  being able to be accessible for wound cleansing and evaluation follow up.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Unbroken skin;

          -  Full-thickness skin loss and damage to muscle, bone or/and any supporting structures
             (e.g. tendon, joint capsule);

          -  Wounds with a sinus where the base of the wound is not visible;

          -  Wounds to be healed by primary intention (e.g. sutured wound, skin grafts and
             skin-graft donor sites);

          -  Wound that was prescribed to be cleansed by irrigation;

          -  Patient with more than one wound;

          -  Patients with a very poor life expectancy or with a clinical condition that might
             interfere with wound healing such as active carcinoma, vasculitis, use of systemic
             corticosteroids, immunosuppressive agents, radiation therapy or chemotherapy within
             the past 30 days.
